Monotonous Stack/Largest Rectangle in Hi.title: Largest Rectangle in Histogram
Monotonous Stack/Largest Rectangle in Hi.body:
Problem
LintCode 122. Largest Rectangle in Histogram
https://www.lintcode.com/problem/largest-rectangle-in-histogram/description
Solution
class Solution {
public:
    /**
     * @param height: A list of integer
     * @return: The area of largest rectangle in the histogram
     */
    int largestRectangleArea(vector &heights) {
        // write your code here

        /**
         *
         *         *
         *       * *
         *       * *
         *       * *   *
         *   *   * * * *
         *   * * * * * *
         *   2 1 5 6 2 3
         *
         *
         *   Let's consider the siutation that the stack has 1, 5, and 6, and
         *   then we see 2, the number that is less than 6.
         *
         *   1st:   2nd:
         *
         *    *
         *    *     * *
         *    *     * *
         *    *     * *
         *    *     * *
         *    *     * *
         *    6     5 6
         *
         *    1x6   2x5
         *
         *    Let' consider the situation that the stack has 1, 2, 3, and
         *    then we use a dummy number, -1, to trigger the last examination.
         *
         *   1st:   2nd:       3rd:
         *

Problem
LintCode 676. Decode Ways II
https://www.lintcode.com/problem/decode-ways-ii/description
Solution
class Solution {
public:
    Solution()
      : mod(1000000007)
    { }

    /**
     * @param s: a message being encoded
     * @return: an integer
     */
    int numDecodings(string &s) {
        // write your code here

        /**
         *            i
         *      *******
         *           (i - 1)
         *  ->  ******
         *           (i - 2)
         *  ->  *****
         *
         *  dp[i]: The number of ways to decode the given substring ending at
         *         the ith letter.
         *
         *  dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + dp[i - 2]
         *
         *
         *  dp[i - 1]:
         *      - s[i]: 0           , get 0
         *      - s[i]: {1, ..., 9} , get dp[i - 1]
         *      - s[i]: *           , get 9 * dp[i - 1]
         *
         *  dp[i - 2]:
         *      - s[i - 1]: 0           , get 0
         *      - s[i - 1]: 1
         *          - s[i]: {0, ..., 9} , get dp[i - 2]
         *          - s[i]: *           , get 9 * dp[i - 2]
         *      - s[i - 1]: 2
         *          - s[i]: {0, ..., 6} , get dp[i - 2]
         *          - s[i]: {7, 8, 9}   , get 0
         *          - s[i]: *           , get 6 * dp[i - 2]
         *      - s[i - 1]: {3, ..., 9} , get 0
         *      - s[i - 1]: *
         *          - s[i]: {0, ..., 6} , get 2 * dp[i - 2]
         *          - s[i]: {7, 8, 9}   , get dp[i - 2]
         *          - s[2]: *           , get 15 * dp[i - 2]
         *
         */

        int n = s.length();

        if (n == 0) {
            return 0;
        }
